HEADWORD: Bootless
<hw>Boot"less</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Boot</er> profit.]</ety> <def>Unavailing; unprofitable; useless;
without advantage or success.</def> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I'll follow him no more with <qex>bootless</qex> prayers.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Boot"less*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Boot"less*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bootlick</ent>⟦br⟧
